        <section name="Introduction">

            The Java Pairing Based Cryptography Library (jPBC) is:
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        a <font style="font-weight: bold;color:red">Java Port</font> of the
                        <a href="http://crypto.stanford.edu/pbc/">Pairing-Based Cryptography Library (PBC)</a>
                        library developed by <a href="http://crypto.stanford.edu/~blynn/">Ben Lynn</a>.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        a <font style="font-weight: bold;color:red">Java Wrapper</font> on the
                        <a href="http://crypto.stanford.edu/pbc/">PBC</a>
                        library. This means that you you can delegate the pairing computation to PBC.
                        Have a look
                        <a href="./docs/pbcwrapper.html">here</a>
                        to know how to use the wrapper.
                    </p>
                </li>

            </ul>

            jPBC consists of the following three core modules:
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jpbc-api</font> :
                    it contains the Application Program Interfaces (API).
                </li>

                <li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jpbc-plaf</font> :
                    it contains the port implementation of the API.
                </li>

                <li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jpbc-pbc</font> :
                    it contains the wrapper implementation of the API.
                </li>
	    </ul>
	    and the following support modules:
	    <ul>
        	<li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jpbc-crypto</font> :
                    it contains the implementation of some pairing based crypto-systems.
                    Have a look
                    <a href="./schemes/schemes.html">here</a>
                    to start.
                </li>
		<li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jpbc-benchmark</font> :
                    it contains the suite used to benchmark jPBC.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green">jpbc-android</font> :
                    it contains an Android App to benchmark jPBC on any Android 2.1+ terminals.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

